		<b>Comment By Philip Doty, 10-28-05</b>
		<p>Jenny - I certainly agree with you about the plight of the Rocky Mountain area sports fans. Often there is not much to root for in the way of teams. However, I believe you have not yet considered the University of Montana Grizzlies football team. They have been a consistently high ranking team and been to the national playoffs for a number of years now. Plus the team has won 2 national championhips and placed second twice. So there you have it. Root for the University of Montana football team! Oh - we also have a mascot that has been national mascot of the year two years running now! Monte is his name.</p>
		
		<b>Comment By Park City Value, 10-29-05</b>
		<p>I know that the festival is a money maker but how much good does it do for the home town people.  If possible most people leave town...</p>
		
